        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Ownership</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Car loan: you own the vehicle from day one. Novated lease: the leasing company owns the vehicle during the lease; you own it after paying the residual. Finance lease: the finance company owns the vehicle; you purchase it at the end by paying the residual. Chattel mortgage: you own the vehicle from day one (lender holds a mortgage).</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Who Can Use It</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Car loan: anyone — employees, self-employed, retirees, Centrelink recipients. Novated lease: salaried employees only, with employer agreement. Finance lease: businesses with an ABN. Chattel mortgage: businesses with an ABN (GST-registered for GST claims).</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Tax Treatment</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Car loan (personal): no tax deductions — interest and depreciation are not deductible for personal use. Novated lease: payments from pre-tax salary reduce taxable income; EVs are FBT-exempt; running costs also salary sacrificed. Finance lease: lease payments are deductible; GST claimed on payments; residual is not deductible. Chattel mortgage: interest deductible; GST claimed upfront on purchase; vehicle depreciated over effective life (8 years for cars).</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">GST</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Car loan (personal): you pay GST on the purchase price. Novated lease: no GST on purchase price (saving approximately 10%). Finance lease: GST claimed progressively on each lease payment. Chattel mortgage: full GST claimed upfront in your next BAS — on a $60,000 vehicle, that is approximately $5,454 back immediately.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">End of Term</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Car loan: car is yours, nothing more to pay. Novated lease: pay the residual to own the car, start a new lease, or return the vehicle. Finance lease: pay the residual, refinance, or return. Chattel mortgage: pay the optional balloon (if applicable), or the car is already fully owned if no balloon was set.</p>
