            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">You are retired, receiving Centrelink benefits, or have irregular income not suited to salary sacrifice</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">You are buying an older used car that may not meet lease criteria</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">You value simplicity over tax optimisation — a car loan is the easiest to understand and manage</span></li>
          </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">For the majority of personal car buyers in Australia, a secured car loan remains the most appropriate choice. It is the simplest structure, offers competitive rates (from 4.99% p.a. secured), and provides full ownership flexibility from day one.</p>
        </section>
