            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Choosing a finance lease because "it sounds like renting" without understanding the residual obligation — you are responsible for the residual payment at the end, or you must return the vehicle.</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Ignoring the total cost and focusing only on weekly payments — a longer lease term reduces weekly payments but increases total cost significantly.</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Not comparing a car loan against a lease before committing — for some situations, a simple car loan is cheaper on a total cost basis despite missing the tax benefits.</span></li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light">Assuming dealer finance is the only option — dealers rarely offer leases or chattel mortgages, so their comparison is already limited.</span></li>
